# PlanForge Workflow

- **When the user uses /p or asks for a plan/design/structure:**  
  Do **not** write a plan or design document yourself. You **must** run `planforge plan "<goal>"` (or `.cursor/skills/p/scripts/run_plan.sh` with the goal as arguments). The CLI creates `.cursor/plans/<summary>-<hash>.plan.md`. After it completes, read that file and summarize or reference it in your reply. If the command fails, report the error and suggest fixes.
- **When the user uses /i or asks for implementation:**  
  Use the implementer (planforge implement or the i skill) as configured; do not bypass it. When implementing (/i), prefer following the plan in `.cursor/plans/` (see index.json `activePlan` or the latest `.plan.md`).
